	  	      		<p>[...] But I&#8217;ve come to the realization that I enjoy my ability to slip into a hazy, unclear world. When I first got glasses, in elementary school, the eye doctor suggested that I not wear them all the time, so I wouldn&#8217;t become dependent on them (which is apparently a myth; see #14). At first, I wore them only for portions of the school day, but eventually decided I needed them for sports (well, tee-ball). Gradually, I began wearing them almost all the time. [...]</p>
