      	<div class="comment_text">
	  	      		<p>These 15 myths are absolutely correct.  Each one has been supported by medical research.  The responses given where people mention a family member or friend who had this condition occur or that are baseless.  You need something called a CONTROL to validate those assumptions.  </p>
<p>There will always be a single patient here or there that goes against what we believe is true. . . but they are anomalies and their results cannot be generalized to the standard population.</p>
